Association Constants (<italic toggle="yes">K</italic> <sub>1</sub> and <italic toggle="yes">K</italic> <sub>2</sub>; 300 K, Toluene-<italic toggle="yes">d</italic> <sub>8</sub>) of Pyridine to <bold>1</bold>,<xref ref-type="bibr" rid="ref8"></xref> <bold>2</bold>, and <bold>3</bold> <xref rid="tbl1-fn1"></xref> K 1 (L mol–1) K 2 (L mol–1) Ni-TPPF20 (1) 7.8 20.5 Ni-TPCF20 (2) 91.1 43.4 Ni-TPIBF20 (3) 441.0 77.5

All values and titration curves are given in the Supporting Information.

Table 1. Association Constants (K₁ and K₂; 300 K, Toluene-d₈) of Pyridine to 1, 2, and 3[^1]

|              | K₁ (L mol⁻¹) | K₂ (L mol⁻¹) |
|--------------|--------------|--------------|
| Ni-TPPF₂₀ (1) | 7.8          | 20.5         |
| Ni-TPCF₂₀ (2) | 91.1         | 43.4         |
| Ni-TPIBF₂₀ (3)| 441.0        | 77.5         |

[^1]: All values and titration curves are given in the [Supporting Information](http://pubs.acs.org/doi/suppl/10.1021/acs.inorgchem.5b01756/suppl_file/ic5b01756_si_001.pdf).
